cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a framework for verifying the predictions of deep learning models, which is a common problem in many deep learning applications. The paper specifically focuses on using deep generative models to verify the outputs of deep discriminative models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses out-of-distribution detection and adversarial example detection, which are common topics in the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper uses conditional variational auto-encoders, which are a type of neural network, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely sub-category.
